## 🔄 Project evolution

### V1. Shiny App (Thesis 2023)

The original application was developed in R with Shiny as the thesis deliverable. It allowed users to visually explore pre-calculated analysis results: the 317 association rules, the table of 11 clinical profiles and a chord diagram by subtypes.

**Limitations:** results were pre-calculated and embedded, so it was not possible to modify parameters, run the pipeline or load new data from the interface.

🔗 [ShinyApps.io](http://0dt2j0-manuel-mar0n0fern0ndez.shinyapps.io/TFMVisualizing_ShinyApp)

---

### V2. Full Web App (FastAPI + HTML)

Complete redesign of the application with the goal of making the pipeline **executable in real time** from the browser, without depending on R or pre-calculated results.

**What changes:**

- The FP-Growth pipeline runs on the server (Python/mlxtend) with configurable parameters
- Data is loaded from the same source as the original thesis (Google Drive) and cached locally
- Computed results are automatically compared against the 11 rules from Table 3 of the thesis
- An interactive force-directed network graph visualization is added
- Integrated clinical and statistical documentation is included within the app

🔗 [melanoma-pipeline.onrender.com](https://melanoma-pipeline.onrender.com)

